# NTU Academic Procedure Chatbot

Vietnamese chatbot grounded on an OWL ontology of academic procedures.
PhoBERT is fine-tuned for token-level **Named Entity Recognition** to detect
mentions of ontology classes in user queries; recognised spans are then
disambiguated against ontology individuals (and their `hasAlias` literals) via
**RapidFuzz**, and per-class **SPARQL** queries fetch the data that is rendered
into a templated reply.

## Architecture

```
user query
    │
    ▼
[ PhoBERT NER ]  →  spans tagged with one of 5 ontology classes
    │
    ▼
[ RapidFuzz ]    →  best individual per (span, class)  (skips low-confidence)
    │
    ▼
[ SPARQL ]       →  per-class fetcher returns structured record
    │
    ▼
[ Renderer ]     →  Vietnamese template; multi-entity blocks concatenated
```

Greetings (keyword heuristic) and out-of-domain queries (no confident match)
short-circuit the pipeline with canned responses.

## Layout

```
src/
  config.py                 paths, model and training hyperparameters
  pipeline.py               end-to-end answer() function
  ontology/
    loader.py               owlready2 load + label-map utilities
    fuzzy.py                rapidfuzz index per class (canonical + aliases)
    queries.py              per-class SPARQL fetchers
    response.py             reply templates + multi-entity composition
  data/
    templates.py            sentence templates and surface-noise functions
    build_dataset.py        synthetic train/test JSONL generator
  ner/
    dataset.py              HF Dataset + sub-word ↔ word label alignment
    train.py                fine-tuning loop with seqeval metrics
    evaluate.py             entity-level benchmark on test split
    inference.py            text → entities decoder
  api/server.py             FastAPI server (serves web/index.html)
  utils/preprocessing.py    optional Vietnamese cleanup utilities
  viz/training_curves.py    train/val loss + accuracy + F1 plots
web/index.html              chat UI wired to /chat
ontology/                   the OWL/XML ontology source
dataset/                    generated train.jsonl / test.jsonl
```

## Workflow

```bash
uv sync                                 # install deps (CUDA wheels via uv index)
uv run build-dataset                    # regenerate dataset/train.jsonl + test.jsonl
uv run train                            # fine-tune PhoBERT NER
uv run evaluate                         # entity-level benchmark on the test split
uv run serve --reload                   # start the chatbot at http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

The dataset builder is deterministic (`--seed`); rerun whenever
`ontology/Ontology_AcademicProcedure_v6.owx` changes.

## Metrics

Training curves (`out/training/training_curves.png`) plot train loss, val loss,
val accuracy and val F1 (macro). Evaluation (`out/evaluation/`) emits
`test_metrics.json` (token accuracy, entity-level precision/recall/F1 micro &
macro) and the seqeval `classification_report.txt`.
